  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Warehouse Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Perform loading and unloading of goods (requires physical strength and stamina).</li><li>Handle inventory management, including sorting, packing, and organizing items in the warehouse.</li><li>Ensure proper documentation for incoming and outgoing shipments.</li><li>Maintain cleanliness and safety standards in the warehouse environment.</li><li>Operate warehouse equipment (e.g., forklifts, pallet jacks) where required.</li><li>Collaborate with team members to ensure efficient operations during the night shift.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Physically fit and able to perform manual labor.</li><li>Comfortable with night shift work (including extended hours if needed).</li><li>Ability to work in a fast-paced and physically demanding environment.</li><li>Attention to detail and good organizational skills.</li><li>Previous experience in warehouse operations is an advantage but not mandatory.</li><li>Must adhere to safety guidelines and company policies.</li><li>Working Hours:Night Shift</li><li><u><strong>主要职责：</strong></u></li><li>负责货物的装卸工作（需要一定的体力和耐力）。</li><li>进行库存管理，包括分类、包装及整理仓库物品。</li><li>确保所有进出货物的文件记录准确无误。</li><li>维持仓库的清洁和安全标准。</li><li>必要时操作仓库设备（如叉车、托盘车等）。</li><li>与团队成员协作，确保夜班期间的运营效率。</li><li>职位要求：</li><li>身体健康，能够从事体力劳动。</li><li>能接受夜班工作（包括必要时加班）。</li><li>能够适应快节奏和体力要求高的工作环境。</li><li>具有良好的注意力和组织能力。</li><li>有仓库相关工作经验者优先，但不是必需的。</li><li>遵守安全规定及公司政策。</li></ul><p>We appreciate your commitment to excellence and attention to detail. Please note that your diligent efforts will contribute significantly to the overall success of our warehouse operations. Only shortlisted candidates will be notified, and all resumes received will be used for recruitment purposes only.</p><p>EA License ID :18C9520</p><p>EA Registration ID :R1765753</p>",
